# ADR 001 — Use pgvector over Pinecone

## Status
Accepted

## Context
ClarityDesk needs vector storage for RAG-based chat.
Options considered: Pinecone, Weaviate, pgvector.

## Decision
Use pgvector as a PostgreSQL extension.

## Reasoning
- Keeps the stack simple — one database for relational + vector data
- No additional managed service or API key needed
- PostgreSQL is already our primary database
- pgvector supports cosine similarity search sufficient for our scale

## Consequences
- Slightly less scalable than dedicated vector DBs at massive scale
- Acceptable tradeoff for a solo productivity tool
